pneumothorax, which generally accumulates\nalong the apical and lateral portions of the lungs.\nSupine radiographs\n• It is important to be familiar with findings that may be present on supine\nradiographs that reflecting presence of pneumothorax.\nTension pneumothorax\n• Is due to a one-way valve mechanism that\nallows air into but not out of the pleural space,\nthereby allowing the pleural pressure to exceed\natmospheric pressure.\n• Findings at chest radiography that may suggest a\ntension pneumothorax include:\n1. collapse of the ipsilateral lung\n2. contralateral mediastinal deviation\n3. inversion of the ipsilateral diaphragm.\n74"}